vanced packaging, test, and assembly; supply variability could raise unit costs or force expensive alternatives.'),(199,0,'Wafer fabrication dependency on TSMC and GF',NULL,NULL,1,43,NULL,'2026-06-20 20:10:31.393782',NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(200,0,'Programmable logic IC foundry dependency on TSMC, UMC, Samsung',NULL,NULL,1,43,NULL,'2026-06-20 20:10:33.224097',NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(201,0,'Wafer foundry supply ÔÇô TSMC (7nm and below)',NULL,NULL,1,43,124,'2026-06-21 16:19:16.479891',NULL,0,NULL,'Item 1A: \'We utilize third-party wafer foundries to fabricate the silicon wafers for all of our products. We rely on Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited (TSMC) for the production of all wafers for microprocessor and GPU products at 7 nanometer (nm) or smaller nodesÔÇŽ\''),(202,0,'Wafer foundry supply ÔÇô GlobalFoundries (>7nm)',NULL,NULL,1,43,125,'2026-06-21 16:23:24.115223',NULL,0,NULL,'Item 1A: \'We utilize third-party wafer foundries to fabricate the silicon wafers for all of our products. We rely ÔÇŽ primarily on GLOBALFOUNDRIES Inc. (GF) for wafers for microprocessor and GPU products manufactured at process nodes larger than 7 nm.\''),(203,0,'Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited (TSMC) wafer production for HPC, FPGA and adaptive SoC products',NULL,NULL,1,43,12,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'Item 1. Business - Manufacturing Arrangements: \'We utilize Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited (TSMC) for the production of wafers for our HPC, FPGA and adaptive SoC products and GLOBALFOUNDRIES Inc. (GF), with respect to wafer purchases for our HPC products at the 12 nm and 14 nm technology nodes. Additionally, we utilize TSMC, United Microelectronics Corporation (UMC) and Samsung Electronics Co., Ltd. for the production of our ICs in the form of programmable logic devices.\''),(204,0,'GLOBALFOUNDRIES Inc. (GF) wafer purchases for HPC products at 12 nm and 14 nm technology nodes',NULL,NULL,1,43,125,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'Item 1. Business - Manufacturing Arrangements: \'We utilize Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited (TSMC) for the production of wafers for our HPC, FPGA and adaptive SoC products and GLOBALFOUNDRIES Inc. (GF), with respect to wafer purchases for our HPC products at the 12 nm and 14 nm technology nodes. Additionally, we utilize TSMC, United Microelectronics Corporation (UMC) and Samsung Electronics Co., Ltd. for the production of our ICs in the form of programmable logic devices.\''),(205,0,'United Microelectronics Corporation (UMC) production of ICs (programmable logic devices)',NULL,NULL,1,43,126,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'Item 1. Business - Manufacturing Arrangements: \'We utilize Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited (TSMC) for the production of wafers for our HPC, FPGA and adaptive SoC products and GLOBALFOUNDRIES Inc. (GF), with respect to wafer purchases for our HPC products at the 12 nm and 14 nm technology nodes. Additionally, we utilize TSMC, United Microelectronics Corporation (UMC) and Samsung Electronics Co., Ltd. for the production of our ICs in the form of programmable logic devices.\''),(206,0,'Samsung Electronics Co., Ltd. production of ICs (programmable logic devices)',NULL,NULL,1,43,13,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'Item 1. Business - Manufacturing Arrangements: \'We utilize Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited (TSMC) for the production of wafers for our HPC, FPGA and adaptive SoC products and GLOBALFOUNDRIES Inc. (GF), with respect to wafer purchases for our HPC products at the 12 nm and 14 nm technology nodes. Additionally, we utilize TSMC, United Microelectronics Corporation (UMC) and Samsung Electronics Co., Ltd. for the production of our ICs in the form of programmable logic devices.\'');
